PACKAGING SYSTEMS AND ENTERPRISES, INC., Respondent,
v.
OPERATIONAL SOLUTIONS, INC., et al., Appellants. WD 82077 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Order filed: June 28, 2019 Matthew W. Geary, Kansas City, for Respondent. Anthony L. Gosserand, Kansas City, for Appellants. Before Division One: Victor C. Howard, Presiding Judge, Lisa White Hardwick, Judge and Gary D. Witt, Judge

ORDER

PER CURIAM:

Operational Solutions appeals the judgment of the Jackson County Circuit Court overruling its motion to vacate/quash a foreign judgment. It complains on appeal that the New Jersey court should not have entered the judgment at issue because it did not have personal jurisdiction over Operational Solutions. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum has been provided to the parties. The judgment is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
